Usage: trigger <connection_number>

Triggers (activates) a connection on the current map. This may include objects such as gates, spikes, teleporters, pits, doors, and similar archetypes.

This command is useful when a DM wants to activate an archetype (gate, spikes, pit, door, etc.) directly, without needing to locate and use the corresponding in-map trigger (such as a pedestal, altar, lever, button, or inventory check).

To determine the correct connection number, use the dump command on the map archetype.

Example:
 trigger 2

This activates the archetype associated with connection 2 (i.e., connected 2).

See also: dump